", "experiences/4/jobDescription": "I joined The Old English Pub when it was just four walls, no setup, no systems. Together with the owner, I built everything from scratch: layout, supplier network, menus, systems, staffing, and structure. Once launched, I ran the business completely hands-on, without any back office or departmental support.\n\nI handled hiring, training, scheduling, payroll, stock control, purchasing, marketing, and cost management, as well as leading daily operations, ensuring service standards, and building strong supplier and customer relationships. It was full ownership of every detail, every day.\n\nThis experience taught me how to build something from the ground up and run it like my own. I learned to lead by doing, solve problems fast, and keep both quality and profitability high, all in a fast-moving environment.", "experiences/4/jobEndedOn": "1-2020", "experiences/4/jobLocation": "Bangkok Metropolitan Area, Thailand", "experiences/4/jobStartedOn": "6-2018", "experiences/4/jobStillWorking": "false", "experiences/4/title": "General Manager                                Pub & Restaurant", "experiences/5/companyId": "19079717", "experiences/5/companyIndustry": "Entertainment Providers", "experiences/5/companyLink1": "https://www.linkedin.com/company/4descapes/", "experiences/5/companyName": "4D Escapes", "experiences/5/companySize": "11-50", "experiences/5/companyUrn": "urn:li:fsd_company:19079717", "experiences/5/companyWebsite": "https://4descapes.com", "experiences/5/employmentType": "Full-time", "experiences/5/jobDescription": "I relocated to England and took on the role as General Manager for 4D Escapes, a VR entertainment company with venues in both Northampton and Dublin. I managed operations across both cities, commuting regularly, and was responsible for all aspects of the business, from daily operations and team leadership to handling large group and corporate bookings.\n\nThe role required strong organizational skills, adaptability, and a hospitality mindset, as many customers came in groups expecting top-tier service and coordination. It was a rewarding experience both professionally and personally, as living in a new country taught me a lot and added another layer to my management journey.", "experiences/5/jobEndedOn": "6-2018", "experiences/5/jobLocation": "Northampton, Storbritannien", "experiences/5/jobLocationCountry": "IE", "experiences/5/jobStartedOn": "12-2017", "experiences/5/jobStillWorking": "false", "experiences/5/logo": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C560BAQE_qebTCbwOJw/company-logo_400_400/company-logo_400_400/0/1630589479534/4descapes_logo?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=1e--amosR8mZ4NNK-Vv0Jo5BHbaEI2bBLh0gfChRR9U", "experiences/5/title": "General Manager", "experiences/6/companyName": "Cajutan", "experiences/6/employmentType": "Contract", "experiences/6/jobDescription": "A friend of mine had started Cajutan, a Swedish restaurant in Bangkok, but was struggling due to issues with the previous management. I stepped in during a gap between jobs, acting more or less as a hands-on consultant.\n\nDuring my six months there, I led a full renovation of the venue, introduced a new menu, and helped restructure the team, bringing in trusted staff from Flann O’Brien’s, which had just closed due to a landlord contract issue. I focused on improving operations, boosting guest experience, and creating a more sustainable business model.\n\nAlthough the venue was ultimately too small for me long term, it was a valuable learning experience where I had full creative and operational freedom to turn things around quickly.", "experiences/6/jobEndedOn": "12-2017", "experiences/6/jobLocation": "Bangkok", "experiences/6/jobStartedOn": "7-2017", "experiences/6/jobStillWorking": "false", "experiences/6/title": "Restaurant Manager", "experiences/7/companyId": "1919918", "experiences/7/companyIndustry": "Events Services", "experiences/7/companyLink1": "https://www.linkedin.com/company/impact-exhibition-and-c